Exp_Guess: I think the study wanted to measure our memory abilities while also being distracted and completing a task. I also think it could have been about the ability to remember a task or carry out an exercise, while not physically doing it while you learn.
Results_Guess: I think the results would show that tasks that are done in a certain order that are similar to each other are easier to remember. For example, lifting your left leg was easier to remember after the person lifted their right leg. However, when there were unrelated tasks such as a spin and jump it was much harder to remember.
Understanding: The study was easy to follow and very self-explanatory. It was a little weird to have no audio, but I am assuming that it is part of the study.
Strategies: I tried to remember the steps of the person in categories, which made certain movements easier to remember. For example, if he lifted a leg I tried to group the three movements that followed into a category.
